1
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,940
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,940 --> 00:00:14,900
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,580
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:20,580
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,460
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:31,580
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:31,580 --> 00:00:35,420
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:40,100
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:40,460 --> 00:00:44,420
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:50,820
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:54,980
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:55,220 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:05,660
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:12,460
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:17,420
=Episode 7=
(This story is entirely fictional.)

17
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:18,960
Prefect,

18
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:20,240
he is deceiving the public
with wicked words.

19
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,040
He should be arrested and punished!

20
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,760
You're right.

21
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:22,720
Li Yunhe,

22
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,040
is this your plan?

23
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,160
Hold on!

24
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,480
What are you doing here?

25
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:29,960
Go back, now.

26
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:32,360
Prefect,

27
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:34,880
Li Yunhe is the Zhou live-in son-in-law.

28
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,720
When you inquired

29
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,720
about strategies, Prefect,

30
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,080
he was merely proposing a response.

31
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:40,600
Even if his words were incorrect,

32
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,040
it hardly amounts to a crime.

33
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,480
Why must he be thrown into prison?

34
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,720
Moreover,

35
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,920
the matter of Li Yunhe tearing down
the proclamation

36
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,440
is already full of doubtful points.

37
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:52,600
That is indeed a questionable matter.

38
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:54,760
Wait.

39
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,040
And who might you be?

40
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,320
I'm...

41
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:01,280
She's my personal maid.

42
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,320
Her words don't count.

43
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:08,800
Guards!

44
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:12,320
Seize these two
who are disrupting the court!

45
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:13,480
Hold it.

46
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,040
Prefect,

47
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:17,800
I believe Li Yunhe's method is feasible.

48
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,600
Well, well,

49
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,840
you again?

50
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:22,560
Just now,

51
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:23,880
you were exchanging glances

52
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,000
with the Zhous' maid right here.

53
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,200
Now you jump out to help Li Yunhe?

54
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,320
Who the hell are you?

55
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,680
Prefect,

56
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,240
recently, the areas around Feng City
have been flooded.

57
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,520
Refugees are pouring in ceaselessly.

58
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:37,320
The grain price issue is already
a thorn in our side.

59
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:39,920
Why not try Li Yunhe's method first?

60
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,920
What's the harm
in making a last-ditch effort?

61
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,680
Better than sitting around
awaiting our doom.

62
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,760
That's absurd.

63
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,720
How can matters of people's livelihood
be treated as a game?

64
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,600
He's just a live-in son-in-law
of the Zhou household.

65
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,480
What does he know about statecraft?

66
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,680
Could it be that you already

67
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,320
have a good plan to deal with this?

68
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:56,720
I...

69
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,400
I don't know

70
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,160
whether Li Yunhe tore down
the proclamation willingly,

71
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,600
but since he remains calm
in the face of crisis,

72
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:04,640
presumably,

73
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:06,720
he's quite confident

74
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,480
in the strategy he proposed.

75
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,840
If it doesn't work,

76
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,080
and public unrest brews,

77
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,160
who will bear the consequences?

78
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,240
Originally,
I had the people in my heart,

79
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,840
but unfortunately,
you're all too foolish.

80
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,120
Forget it then.

81
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:23,760
It seems I must

82
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,040
visit the prison after all.

83
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,040
Guards!

84
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,440
Put the shackles on me, then.

85
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,040
Hold on!

86
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,040
Prefect,

87
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,200
I think

88
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,200
we should follow

89
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,680
Li Yunhe's method to proceed.

90
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,500
What's going on?

91
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:44,640
My lord,
what is your view on this matter?

92
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:47,840
I don't really understand statecraft,

93
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,440
but Chen is right.

94
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:52,040
There's no better way now.

95
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,320
Then let's try it as he said.

96
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,440
(So what if it incites a rebellion?)

97
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,560
(They're just
a bunch of lowlifes anyway.)

98
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,720
(At worst, I'll have Father
send troops to suppress them.)

99
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,680
(By then,
the people's anger and resentment)

100
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,640
(will all be pinned
on Li Yunhe and the Zhous.)

101
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,960
(Let's see if he survives that.)

102
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,840
We'll do this

103
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,400
dragon boat race

104
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,680
and implement

105
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,320
work relief.

106
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,320
The government will help post notices

107
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:16,720
to raise grain prices.

108
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,360
Yes.

109
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,640
Li Yunhe.

110
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,640
Prefect.

111
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,240
You go back and rest well.

112
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:26,120
I'll summon you if there's any matter.

113
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:26,840
Understood.

114
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,400
I take my leave then.

115
00:04:37,380 --> 00:04:41,060
(Zhou Manor)

116
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:49,960
Hey,

117
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:51,240
what are you busy with?

118
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,280
I don't have time to explain now.

119
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,640
I'll help you pack first.

120
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:55,520
You need to hurry up

121
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,720
and flee

122
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,120
before the city gates close.

123
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,840
Why should I flee?

124
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,240
I'm doing just fine.

125
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:03,720
Besides,

126
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,360
I don't want to leave you.

127
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,000
How can you be so foolish?

128
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,080
Why did you have to

129
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,400
tear down that government proclamation?

130
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:15,600
Anyone can see

131
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,440
that Lu Qifeng and the Feng City Prefect

132
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,920
set it up to frame you.

133
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:19,960
You also said

134
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,480
once the disaster relief fails

135
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,360
and stirs public anger,

136
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,800
you'll be the first one

137
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,040
to be beheaded!

138
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,240
What are you panicking about?

139
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,760
If they dare

140
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:31,400
put my name out there,

141
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,080
before long,

142
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,040
my name

143
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,080
will be known throughout the land.

144
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,160
Yeah, you'll be wanted by everyone,

145
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,560
infamous for eternity.

146
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:41,560
No.

147
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,960
My good reputation will spread

148
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,000
across the world.

149
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,640
Where on earth
do you get this confidence?

150
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:48,680
Don't worry.

151
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,480
I have a life principle, which is

152
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:54,520
that a gentleman
never stands beneath a crumbling wall.

153
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:57,120
Besides, if there was real danger,

154
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,240
I'd have fled long ago.

155
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,440
Yeah, keep boasting.

156
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,720
Never mind.

157
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,120
If you won't leave, then don't.

158
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:03,840
At worst,

159
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,760
I'll just think of ways
to pull some strings

160
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,040
and work my connections.

161
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,240
(She's merely a hired hand
from the Zhou Manor.)

162
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,320
(Why does her manner of speaking)

163
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,960
(sound so much like the Zhou heiress?)

164
00:06:23,340 --> 00:06:24,400
(Xianquan Tavern)

165
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,400
(Xianquan Tavern)
Yunzhuo.

166
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:28,480
Your incognito visit this time

167
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,000
is way too low-key.

168
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:31,760
That idiot Prefect from earlier

169
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,360
was clearly in cahoots

170
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,600
with the Marquis House.

171
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,160
Why didn't you just chop his head off?

172
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:36,480
Nonsense.

173
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:37,960
A court minister

174
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,360
can't be beheaded on a whim.

175
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,960
He holds the position
and performs his duties.

176
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,360
Moreover,

177
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,440
he did heed Li Yunhe's advice.

178
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:48,360
That shows he can still be redeemed.

179
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:50,280
Li Yunhe

180
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:51,760
really has some substance.

181
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:53,880
It's one thing
to be good at selling goods,

182
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,080
but he can also match verses.

183
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,120
He really is

184
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,000
a man of true talent and learning.

185
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,280
Just matching a line

186
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,280
counts as true talent and learning?

187
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,320
Your standard of judgment

188
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:04,680
is a bit too low, isn't it?

189
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:06,720
You were at the scene today,

190
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:08,160
and you couldn't match it either.

191
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,240
Moreover, Li Yunhe

192
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,720
answered the Prefect's questions

193
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,000
with clear logic

194
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,160
and a sharp mind.

195
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,080
Even you were full of praise.

196
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,160
Zhao Ziyao,

197
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,800
the longer you're out here,

198
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,480
the more insolent you become.

199
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,480
Fine, I'm sorry.

200
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,320
I truly think

201
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,400
Li Yunhe's potential
goes far beyond that.

202
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:30,280
How about we castrate him
and bring him into the palace,

203
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:32,320
so he can keep me company and amuse me?

204
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:33,560
That's enough.

205
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,160
Go back and rest.

206
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:36,760
You're a young lady,

207
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,920
yet you keep roaming around every day

208
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,920
without even changing your clothes?

209
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:39,760
It's just that

210
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,200
I don't have any comfortable clothes.

211
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,240
Well, Li Yunhe is to blame.

212
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:45,720
He sells Gambiered Silk,
and he's still being so stingy,

213
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:47,120
doing that pre-sale nonsense.

214
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,600
It's truly infuriating.

215
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,040
But on the other hand,

216
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,080
the quality
of this batch of Gambiered Silk

217
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,240
is indeed quite good.

218
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,920
I almost regret

219
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,960
revoking their imperial supplier status.

220
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,320
Send men
to keep a close watch on Li Yunhe

221
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,360
and the Marquis House.

222
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,920
Report to me at once
if there's any news.

223
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,120
Yes, Your Majesty.

224
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,560
The Prefect actually
went through with it?

225
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,320
Absolutely true.

226
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:23,640
The Prefect is now

227
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:25,160
sending people everywhere
to post notices,

228
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,960
raising the grain prices.

229
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,280
Interesting.

230
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,200
Truly interesting.

231
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,160
My lord,

232
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,280
now the Prefect

233
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,520
not only has people
posting notices everywhere,

234
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:38,520
but also says that Li Yunhe,

235
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,120
the folk talent, proposed the strategy.

236
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,400
And now,

237
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,600
many of the city's commoners

238
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,080
are cursing
this conscienceless scoundrel.

239
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:46,880
Good.

240
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:47,960
Very good.

241
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:49,880
Li Yunhe

242
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,760
likes raising grain prices, huh?

243
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,600
Send men out.

244
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,520
Have the neighboring
prefectures and counties

245
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:59,600
ship all their grain in.

246
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,320
Have them ship in as much as they have.

247
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,320
We'll sell it all to the government.

248
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,480
That's brilliant, my lord.

249
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,080
Right now, grain prices
in the surrounding areas are low.

250
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,480
We buy low

251
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:13,080
and sell high to the government.

252
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,280
All this gleaming silver

253
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,880
is money for the taking.

254
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:19,920
Once Li Yunhe's reputation
stinks to high heaven,

255
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,880
even if the Zhou family
wants to protect him,

256
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,080
they'll have to think twice
about the consequences.

257
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:29,080
I take my leave then, my lord.

258
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,560
My lord.

259
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,080
The situation now

260
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,520
is all under your control.

261
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,080
I shall take my leave as well.

262
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,280
Take care, Xie.

263
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:40,000
With the situation as it is,

264
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,960
don't you plan to make a big profit?

265
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,600
It's blood money.

266
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,120
I disdain to earn it.

267
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,320
Oh, Xie,

268
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,200
don't take this the wrong way,

269
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,120
but your family
is the wealthiest in Feng City.

270
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,040
In the way of business,

271
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,680
no one ever complains
about having too much money?

272
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:58,680
As long as your family
cooperates with my Marquis House,

273
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:01,720
I guarantee
you'll rake it in hand over fist.

274
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,240
My father entrusted the business to me,

275
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,880
teaching me to take benevolence
and righteousness as my foundation.

276
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,360
For me to hype grain prices with you

277
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,720
and frame Li Yunhe,

278
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,560
this must absolutely not be done.

279
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:13,800
It's the government buying
at a high price.

280
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,880
As they say, the people
shouldn't fight the officials.

281
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:17,120
Not to mention

282
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,760
that my Marquis House is backing it.

283
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,560
As long as you don't

284
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:23,520
come forward
to lower the grain prices...

285
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:25,080
Fine.

286
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,280
I agree then.

287
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:26,880
Alright.

288
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:27,720
Farewell.

289
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:34,720
The money?

290
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,280
My Marquis House earns it.

291
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,080
As for the infamy,

292
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:42,600
Li Yunhe will have to shoulder it.

293
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:46,980
(Today's grain price:
180 coins per hodful)

294
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,000
(Xinfeng Grain Shop)
Grain price is 180 coins per hodful.

295
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:49,680
It's all because

296
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,080
of that worthless Li Yunhe's idea!

297
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:51,480
Yeah!

298
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,400
Let's get Li Yunhe!

299
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,500
Where is your conscience?

300
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,880
- Let's beat him up!
- Get him!

301
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:00,000
(Zhou Manor)
Li Yunhe, come out now!

302
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,080
- Li Yunhe, get out here!
- Li Yunhe, get out here!

303
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,720
Li Yunhe,

304
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,360
with things as they are now,

305
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,480
how can you still be in the mood

306
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,600
to be drinking tea here?

307
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:20,600
Hey.

308
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,560
Why can't I enjoy some tea?

309
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:26,120
The front gate of the Zhou Manor
is packed with people,

310
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,080
and they're all cursing you.

311
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,200
After the government notice went out,

312
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,320
this afternoon, the grain price

313
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,160
has already risen
to 200 coins per hodful.

314
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:34,800
How could it have risen so much?

315
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,000
How?

316
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,720
How am I supposed to know?

317
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,240
Chunxiang, what does the Prefect say?

318
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,120
Mr. Li,

319
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,320
the steward
just inquired with the Prefect.

320
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,200
The Prefect says

321
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,120
we can continue posting notices

322
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,240
and continue raising prices,

323
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,600
but the government
will no longer buy grain.

324
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,040
Because they have no money.

325
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,240
No money?

326
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,400
Wait.

327
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,040
Feng City may have flooding this year,

328
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,120
but it's still a fertile land.

329
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,480
How can the government

330
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,840
be out of money so quickly?

331
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,120
Hey, Mr. Li,

332
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,240
where are you going so late at night?

333
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:10,840
Chunxiang.

334
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,400
I'm going out to discuss some matters.

335
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,640
Can't you see what's going on?

336
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:15,920
He's messed up

337
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:16,920
and is preparing to flee.

338
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:19,200
Go tell Xingyu about it

339
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,600
and have her sign the divorce letter
right away.

340
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:24,440
Bad news, Your Majesty.

341
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:25,640
The grain on the market

342
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,120
has been completely bought out.

343
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,360
Grain prices are still rising.

344
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:29,520
The common people

345
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:31,520
simply cannot buy any grain.

346
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,240
Those profiteering merchants

347
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,920
are utterly outrageous.

348
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,520
I originally intended
to attract grain merchants

349
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,320
from surrounding areas
to come sell grain quickly

350
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,560
by raising grain prices.

351
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:44,160
As grain prices increased
along with the supply,

352
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,200
those commoners who had money

353
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,320
could buy grain.

354
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,520
I never expected

355
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:50,240
it would turn out like this.

356
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:51,800
Could it be

357
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,440
that someone is meddling
behind the scenes?

358
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:55,920
Have you found anything?

359
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,200
Your Majesty,

360
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,040
the Marquis House

361
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,360
has seemingly dispatched many men

362
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,120
to procure grain from other regions.

363
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,040
The Marquis House

364
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:06,720
is clearly disregarding
people's livelihoods,

365
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:09,400
seeking to exploit this chance
to amass wealth.

366
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,200
You're absolutely right, Yunzhuo.

367
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:14,400
The Marquis House
has no regard for its reputation.

368
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,720
Their greed is truly despicable.

369
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,360
We need to find an opportunity

370
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,120
to give them a proper warning.

371
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,040
Any news from Li Yunhe?

372
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,800
Mr. Li had the Zhous' steward

373
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,200
deliver a letter to the Prefect,

374
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,920
asking the Prefect
to widely post notices

375
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:29,080
to raise grain prices.

376
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:32,200
But the Prefect's Office responded

377
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,720
that the government

378
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,920
already has no money to buy grain.

379
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:38,920
That shouldn't be.

380
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,800
Feng City is a fertile land,

381
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:42,480
so the city government's silver

382
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:44,280
should be able to last
for quite a while.

383
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,880
Your Highness,

384
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:47,880
I don't know about that.

385
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,360
A revolving door of Feng City Prefects

386
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,680
and an ironclad Marquis House...

387
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:55,120
The Marquis title
is hereditary and permanent,

388
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,720
entrenched in Feng City for many years.

389
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:57,920
They're already deeply rooted.

390
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:01,880
If the Feng City government coffers
were full of silver,

391
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,880
that would be the strange thing.

392
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:08,320
Your Majesty,

393
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,560
Li Yunhe requests an audience.

394
00:14:10,080 --> 00:14:12,520
Li Yunhe? What's he doing here?

395
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:15,040
Summon him.

396
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:16,480
- Yes.
- Yes.

397
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,000
(Xianquan Tavern)

398
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,560
(Xianquan Tavern)
Mr. Li, what brings you here

399
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,760
so late at night?

400
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:28,000
My apologies for disturbing you
at this late hour.

401
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,720
Firstly, I came to thank you

402
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,880
for speaking up righteously

403
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:31,960
in the government office today.

404
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,160
Secondly,

405
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:34,680
there's a tremendous

406
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,480
opportunity for wealth.

407
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:37,920
I wonder if you

408
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,360
might be interested.

409
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:41,160
Tremendous wealth?

410
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:42,160
Li Yunhe,

411
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,680
you're not planning a rebellion,
are you?

412
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,800
Mr. Li, please don't take offense.

413
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,800
When my sister was little,

414
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,960
she suffered a fright once.

415
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:52,640
She's not quite hinged.

416
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:54,140
I...

417
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,760
I see.

418
00:14:58,560 --> 00:14:59,680
But sir,

419
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:02,240
about your sister's tendency
to speak without thinking,

420
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:03,200
it's best

421
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,160
to keep her from going out too much

422
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:06,640
lest a careless remark be taken

423
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,800
seriously by someone with ill intentions

424
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:10,680
and bring a prison calamity upon you.

425
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:11,560
Don't you agree?

426
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,800
You're absolutely right, Li.

427
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:15,960
Well, after some time,

428
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:16,960
I'll find my sister

429
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,840
a suitable husband

430
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,440
and marry her off.

431
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:55,260
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

432
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:58,620
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

433
00:15:59,140 --> 00:16:01,860
♪Who took the March rain♪

434
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:05,460
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

435
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:08,620
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

436
00:16:08,780 --> 00:16:11,980
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

437
00:16:12,860 --> 00:16:18,780
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

438
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:22,260
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

439
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:25,340
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

440
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:27,780
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

441
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:31,980
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

442
00:16:32,060 --> 00:16:35,340
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

443
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,620
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

444
00:16:39,140 --> 00:16:42,060
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

445
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:48,740
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

446
00:17:15,020 --> 00:17:18,540
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

447
00:17:18,780 --> 00:17:21,940
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

448
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:25,260
♪Who took the March rain♪

449
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:28,780
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

450
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:32,060
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

451
00:17:32,140 --> 00:17:35,860
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

452
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:39,180
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

453
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:42,140
♪As seasons change♪

454
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:45,780
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

455
00:17:45,780 --> 00:17:48,620
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

456
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:51,260
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

457
00:17:51,260 --> 00:17:55,340
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

458
00:17:55,340 --> 00:17:58,660
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

459
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:02,380
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

460
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:05,900
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

461
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:08,780
♪Only for you♪

462
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:12,380
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

463
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:15,260
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

464
00:18:15,380 --> 00:18:17,940
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

465
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:22,020
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

466
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:25,340
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

467
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:28,740
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

468
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:35,260
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

469
00:18:36,340 --> 00:18:40,460
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

470
00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:46,260
♪Your wedding gown♪
